result.execSummary:
The defendant Atwina N.M.I. Coleman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Atwina N.M.I. Coleman is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Atwina N.M.I. Coleman was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes DF ATTY: Daniel James Chapman DF: Atwina N.M.I. Coleman appeared from jail. Case called at 9:08. Includes 15CF483 (prelim), 15CF470, 15CF420, 14CF540, 13CM678, 14CM661. Atty. Chapman updates the court. On 15CF483   Court advises of rights and possible penalties regarding a preliminary hearing.  Court finds DF has freely, voluntarily, and knowingly waived the right to a preliminary hearing, finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the DF probably committed that felony. On 15CF483  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads G to 15CF483 . DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of 15CF483.  ADA Nieskes updates the court as to 2 other pending charges that will not be filed and will be dismissed with prejudice. ADA Nieskes files a letter from the victims and the testing results from 15CF483.Sentencing arguments. Court dismisses without objection 15CF470 and 15CF420 and any current uncharged referrals. Crt orders: 

On 15CF483
2 years probation concurrent with 14CF540. 
Probation is concurrent without prejudice to consecutive sentencing in the event of Probation revocation.
Court notes credit for 43 days against ultimate sentence. 
- Absolute Sobriety, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times . This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- DE to have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Susan and Megan L. and her family or residence. DE not to be within 100 yards of their residence.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  
- Costs plus cost of supervision.
- Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.
- AODA and any recommended follow through. 
- Not to associate with any persons known or suspected to be involved in use, trafficking, dealing or manufacturing of illegal drugs except in a treatment setting.
- Regular and random testing. 
- Maintain current physical and meantal health treatment and take all prescribed medication. 
- Follow any recommended treatment by agent. 

On 14CF540
2 years probation concurrent to 15CF483 and with the same conditions as 15CF483.
- Costs plus the costs of supervision.
  Apply bond money on file.

90 days St. Croix County Jail
Court notes 43 days credit.
- Costs to be paid through probation on 14CF540.

On 13CM678 Court imposes
90 days St. Croix County Jail concurrent with 14CM661.
Court notes 43 days credit.
- Costs to be paid through probation.

*AMENDED*
Includes 14CF527, 14CM661, 14CM652 and14CF540

-It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations,  Wal-Mart in New Richmond WI,  D. Saltness or Susan L.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

- DE will be baseline tested prior to leaving jail. 

-Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

- Defendant to take all prescribed medication and follow all of the treatment plan.

-  Testing upon reasonable suspicion or at the Court's directive. Defendant must pay $5.00 fee at time of each UA test with an officer of the same sex. Testing every Sat. by 5:00pm.

- Subject to periodic welfare checks of minor child. 

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
